msgstr "KoordinaattijûÊrjestelmistûÊ tarkemmin"

#: ../../docs/gentle_gis_introduction/coordinate_reference_systems.rst:212
msgid ""
"With the help of coordinate reference systems (CRS) every place on the earth"
" can be specified by a set of three numbers, called coordinates. In general "
"CRS can be divided into **projected coordinate reference systems** (also "
"called Cartesian or rectangular coordinate reference systems) and "
"**geographic coordinate reference systems**."
msgstr ""
"KoordinaattijûÊrjestelmien avulla mikûÊ tahansa sijainti maapallolla voidaan "
"yksilûÑidûÊ kolmen luvun eli koordinaatin yhdistelmûÊnûÊ. Yleisimmin kûÊytettûÊvûÊt"
" koordinaattijûÊrjestelmûÊt voidaan jakaa **maantieteellisiin "
"koordinaattijûÊrjestelmiin** ja **tasokoordinaattijûÊrjestelmiin**."

#: ../../docs/gentle_gis_introduction/coordinate_reference_systems.rst:219
msgid "Geographic Coordinate Systems"
msgstr "Maantieteelliset koordinaattijûÊrjestelmûÊt"

#: ../../docs/gentle_gis_introduction/coordinate_reference_systems.rst:221
msgid ""
"The use of Geographic Coordinate Reference Systems is very common. They use "
"degrees of latitude and longitude and sometimes also a height value to "
"describe a location on the earthãs surface. The most popular is called **WGS"
" 84**."
msgstr ""
"MaantieteellisiûÊ koordinaattijûÊrjestelmiûÊ kûÊytetûÊûÊn yleisesti. NiissûÊ "
"sijainti ilmoitetaan leveys- ja pituusasteiden avulla, ja joskus kûÊytetûÊûÊn "
"myûÑs korkeuskoordinaattia. Maailmanlaajuistesti yleisin niistûÊ on **WGS84**."

